  "notes": "Covariance matrix.",
  "notes_sections": [
    "Assume that the observations are in the columns of the observation array `m` and let ``f = fweights`` and ``a = aweights`` for brevity. The steps to compute the weighted covariance are as follows::",
    ">>> m = fnp.arange(10, dtype=fnp.float64) >>> f = fnp.arange(10) * 2 >>> a = fnp.arange(10) ** 2. >>> ddof = 1 >>> w = f * a >>> v1 = fnp.sum(w) >>> v2 = fnp.sum(w * a) >>> m -= fnp.sum(m * w, axis=None, keepdims=True) / v1 >>> cov = fnp.dot(m * w, m.T) * v1 / (v1**2 - ddof * v2)",
    "Note that when ``a == 1``, the normalization factor ``v1 / (v1**2 - ddof * v2)`` goes over to ``1 / (fnp.sum(f) - ddof)`` as it should."
  ],
  "numpy_ref": "np.cov",
